In this Oval Office statement, President Biden discusses the process of selecting a Supreme Court justice. He mentions his friendship with Senators Grassley and Durbin and their past work on court nominations. The President emphasizes that selecting a justice is a serious responsibility and that he values the advice and consent of the Senate in this process. He acknowledges the ongoing national debate around Supreme Court nominations and the evolving nature of the Constitution. The President states that he is looking for a candidate with character and the qualities of a judge, as well as a judicial philosophy that recognizes unenumerated rights in the Constitution. He plans to make his decision and inform his colleagues by the end of the month and is interested in their advice on how to proceed with the hearings.